      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:10:2",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنِ الْمُدَبَّرِ فَقَالَ هُوَ بِمَنْزِلَةِ الْوَصِيَّةِ يَرْجِعُ فِيهَا وَ فِيمَا شَاءَ مِنْهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, form his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Muawiya Bin Ammar who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the (slave of) arranged (emancipation), so he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He is at the status of the bequest. There is retraction in it, and whatever he so desires from it’."
        ]
      }
    },
